# Purpose: Direnv configuration for automatic .env file loading
# Scope: Auto-loads environment variables when entering project directory
# Overview: Configures direnv to automatically load the .env file when you cd into this project directory.
#     Uses the 'dotenv' command to load variables from .env file. Optional sections show how to extend
#     with path additions, project root exports, and sourcing additional env files. Ensures consistent
#     environment setup across all development sessions without manual export commands.
# Placeholders: None - this is a minimal configuration
# Usage:
#     1. Copy to project root: cp .envrc.template .envrc
#     2. Allow direnv: direnv allow
#     3. Test: cd .. && cd - (should see "direnv: loading .envrc")
#     4. Remove this header after copying
# Related: .env, .env.example, ENVIRONMENT_STANDARDS.md
# Implementation: Single command loading with optional extensions for advanced use cases

# Load .env file
dotenv

# Unset GITHUB_TOKEN to allow gh CLI to use keyring authentication
# This ensures gh uses the steve-e-jackson account instead of stevej-at-benlabs
unset GITHUB_TOKEN

# Optional: Add project bin/ directory to PATH
# Uncomment if you have local scripts in bin/
# PATH_add bin

# Optional: Export project root directory
# Uncomment if your code needs to reference PROJECT_ROOT
# export PROJECT_ROOT=$(pwd)

# Optional: Load additional environment-specific files
# Uncomment to load .env.local (for local overrides, also gitignored)
# dotenv_if_exists .env.local

# Optional: Load environment-specific files
# Uncomment for development/staging/production specific configs
# dotenv_if_exists .env.development
# dotenv_if_exists .env.staging
# dotenv_if_exists .env.production
